```

## API Reference Pages

### Endpoint Page Structure

Use `api` frontmatter for interactive playground:

```yaml
---
title: "Create Scenario"
api: "POST /scenarios" # Relative to baseUrl in mint.json
description: "Create a new scenario"
---
```

### Parameters & Examples

````mdx
<ParamField body="name" type="string" required>
  Description here
</ParamField>

<ParamField body="is_public" type="boolean" default="false">
  Optional with default
</ParamField>

<RequestExample>
```json
{ "name": "Example" }
````

</RequestExample>

<ResponseExample>
```json 200
{ "id": "scenario_123" }
```
</ResponseExample>
```

## mint.json Key Settings

### Tabs

```json
"tabs": [
  { "name": "API Reference", "url": "api-reference" }
]
```

First tab (Documentation) is implicit/default.

### API Configuration

```json
"api": {
  "baseUrl": "https://api.toughtongueai.com/api/public",
  "auth": { "method": "bearer" },
  "playground": { "mode": "show" }
}
```

### Navigation

Pages must be listed in `navigation` to appear in sidebar.

## Content Guidelines

### Do's

- ✅ Be concise - no filler content
- ✅ Use action-oriented titles ("Create Scenario" not "Scenario Creation")
- ✅ Add `<Note>` for beta features: "Beta: This feature is under development"
- ✅ Link to related pages
- ✅ Use code examples sparingly

### Don'ts

- ❌ Don't hallucinate features (e.g., made-up rate limits)
- ❌ Don't add unnecessary sections
- ❌ Don't exceed ~100 char line length
- ❌ Don't use `{" "}` in MDX
- ❌ Don't import from external TypeScript files

